SATIRE IV A Desence ο] Horace's Satires from the charye ofmalcvolence. Diam, 38 13.c.

This Satire was written by Horace for the purpose of defending himself and Satire from the charge of malevolence. He claims the same right to castigate vice that the Greek poets of the Old Comedy arrogated to themselves, 1-5 ; the same right that Lucilius enjoyed, 6.
